main event: A private pilot reported seeing some lights moving east to west at a high rate of speed south of Greenville, Ohio around 7:00 pm on October 16, 1966.
interesting points: The report was received second-hand from the FAA in Vandalia, Ohio.
An Air Force Lt. was notified and responded, but no further information is available.
The Air Force requested the observer, a Reverend in Richmond, Indiana, to complete a PTD Form 14 for more details.
The Air Force concluded there was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION'.
There is no photograph present in the provided image.
